{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7fc65e87-af50-4403-9824-1be5a329936b","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically captures crash reports — no `createdump` needed.\n\n**Look here for `.ips` crash logs:**\n\n```\n~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/      # user processes\n/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/       # system-wide\n```\n\nFind your app's report:\n\n```bash\nls -lt ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/ | grep <your-app-name>\n```\n\nThe `.ips` files are JSON-formatted and contain the native backtrace, register state, and loaded images.\n\n**Tips:**\n- Reports appear within seconds of the crash.\n- You can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them.\n- If you have `.dwarf` symbols, you can symbolicate the `.ips` file with `atos` to get function names and line numbers.\n\nIf you have a `.ips` file and need help symbolicating the .NET runtime frames, I can walk you through that too.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fa2bf3fe-ecc4-4cd1-b19f-b4edb4ad27b0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, specifically when `createdump` isn't available. This is a diagnostic/knowledge question — I don't need to search a codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.\n\nOn macOS, when a process crashes, the system automatically generates a crash report (`.ips` file). These are stored in specific directories. For NativeAOT apps, `createdump` isn't bundled (it's a CoreCLR tool), so the OS-level crash report is the primary artifact.\n\nKey locations:\n\n\n- `~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` — for user-launched processes\n- `/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` — system-wide\n\nThe files are `.ips` (JSON format on modern macOS) or `.crash` (older format). I can also point the user toward `log show` or Console.app as tools to locate these reports.","outputTokens":481,"requestId":"6402:1DCDBF:DB0C135:F4B35C3:69EC19CE"},"id":"52f7be17-df2b-447d-9f74-e98aa31eda0c","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:33:14.548Z","parentId":"99a56464-ad78-4529-a1e1-f0716fd066bb"}
